<HEAD>Victim Died Four Years After Attack; Two Convicted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men have been found guilty of
murdering a man who died four years after he was attacked and
robbed.
   Reginald Harding Jr., 24, and Christopher Bush, 30, were
convicted in separate trials by Oakland County Circuit Court juries.
   The victim of the 1983 attack, Jeffrey Dudley, 24, died last
summer. Assistant Prosecutor John Slevin argued Dudley's health
deteriorated steadily after the attack in which he was beaten, shot
in the heart and dumped in a sewer.
   Because of the attack, Dudley wore a pacemaker and underwent
surgery eight times. Doctors testified the attack caused permanent
heart damage.
