<HEAD>Passport Officers Arrested For Corruption</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ABIDJAN, Ivory Coast (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   All the members of the passport
office in Minna in east-central Nigeria have been arrested on
charges of selling passports to foreign nationals, Nigerian state
radio reported Friday.
   The report, monitored in Abidjan, said the passport officials
were collecting an illegal fee of about $17 to $24 in addition to
the official $24 charge.
   Police said the fraud was uncovered when immigration officials
arrested Niger nationals who could not speak any of Nigeria's
languages.
