<HEAD>Robber Returns Cash, Caught</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VERONA, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police say they captured a suspect in a
convenience store robbery after he returned the cash minutes after
he took it.
   David J. Rupp, 28, of Verona allegedly demanded money from early
Thursday and punched a customer, police said.
   The man left with cash from the register but soon returned. He
asked if the clerk had called police and placed the cash on the
counter when the clerk said he had not.
   ``You're not going to remember my face, are you?'' the man said
and fled.
   Another customer saw the license on the man's van and called
police, who arrested Rupp.
   Penn Hills Magistrate Rinaldo Secola arraigned Rupp on robbery
and assault charges and sent him to the Allegheny County Jail in
lieu of bond.
