<HEAD>Betty Ford Turns 70 With Party Plans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RANCHO MIRAGE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former first lady Betty Ford, still
recovering from heart bypass surgery last year, was celebrating her
70th birthday Friday with a small party, her secretary said.
   ``Her husband is giving a party for her this evening with a few
friends and family,'' Ann Cullen said.
   Mrs. Ford underwent bypass surgery in November, but returned to
the hospital in December because of bleeding complications. She was
released from Eisenhower Medical Center on Jan. 3.
