<HEAD>North Secretary to Co-Host ABC-TV Show on Upscale and Famous</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fawn Hall, who made her television debut
testifying about former boss Oliver North before a Senate
committee, will be co-host of a network special its producers hope
is an upscale version of ``The Lifestyles of the Rich and Famous.''
   Miss Hall was chosen ``because she is very spontaneous and has a
presence that is indicative she can handle this kind of assignment
with zest and energy,'' Gary Pudney, an ABC television vice
president for specials, said Friday.
   ``M-W Men and Women,'' based upon M and W magazines, will air
the first week in June. Pudney said it is to combine
``Entertainment Tonight,'' ``60 Minutes'' and an upscale version of
the show that displays the opulent lifestyles of the wealthy.
   The other co-hosts are Ron Reagan, the president's son; actress
Jane Seymour; and Danny Sullivan, the cab-driving Indianapolis 500
winner.
   Miss Seymour will be dressed by the newest fashion darling,
French designer Christian Lacroix, as she interviews him. Reagan
will introduce what's in and out, and Sullivan will flash by with
stars and their cars.
   Miss Hall already has taped her segment for the hourlong show _
an interview with a British heiress who gave it all up to live with
her husband, a Masai warrior, outside of Nairobi, Kenya, in East
Africa.
   ``My understanding is it looks just terrific and we're
encouraged by what we hear about Miss Hall's abilities and
encouraged there might be additional opporturnties for her,''
Pudney said.
   ``I think she was picked because of her natural ability to do
this assignment'' although ``I wouldn't have known about her'' if
Miss Hall had not appeared before a Senate committee investigating
the Iran-Contra affair and North's role in it.
