<HEAD>Boy Drives Off Intruder In Defending Little Sister</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police credited a 10-year-old boy with
defending his younger sister after a man broke into their home and
grabbed the girl around the neck.
   Michael King ``chased off a 36-year-old man by hitting him about
the head and back with a stick,'' Officer H.R. Barnett said.
   Keith Strode was being held Friday in the Jefferson County Jail
on a charge of violating his parole, police said.
   After crashing through a window early Wednesday, a man grabbed
Latasha King, 7, as her mother, Wanda King, and Michael tried to
flee, a police report said.
   Once outside, Mrs. King saw the intruder had her daughter around
the neck, and Michael rushed back and drove off the man with a bed
rail slat, the report said.
   ``(The man) ran out the front door,'' Mrs. King said.
   ``Michael wants a set of ``jams,'' you know those long-legged
shorts and a shirt with a long tail. So we are going to go let him
pick out one he wants,'' Mrs. King said.
   Mrs. King said her husband was at work at the time of the
intrusion.
