<TEXT>
   Mikhail S. Gorbachev said Friday that Soviet
troops will begin coming home from Afghanistan on May 15, but he
added the move shouldn't be seen as ``a present to President
Reagan'' for their upcoming summit meeting.
   Soviets interviewed on the streets of Moscow welcomed the news,
