<1ST_LINE>r f BC-KN-Pickens     04-08 0164</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-KN-Pickens,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lakewood Company Denies Pickens Board Seat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKEWOOD, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   KN Energy Inc. stockholders have denied
corporate raider T. Boone Pickens Jr. a seat on the company's board
of directors, the company announced.
   Pickens got support from about 15 percent of the estimated 9.3
million shares voted, Dick Buxton, a KN spokesman, said Thursday.
   Pickens' Amarillo-based Mesa Limited Partnership owns about 4.9
percent of KN's outstanding stock.
   In February, Pickens launched a proxy battle for one of four
available seats on the KN board, following an unsuccessful attempt
to buy the company last December for about $164 million.
   It was the third time KN has spurned an acquisition bid by
Pickens.
   ``We've known for a while that we were going to lose,'' said
Mesa spokesman David Batchelder after Thursday's announcement. But
he also would not rule out another purchase attempt.
   Elected to three-year terms on the KN board were David
Burkholder, Thos. Creigh Jr., Jordan L. Haines and William J. Hybl.
</TEXT>
