<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Grain and soybean futures prices advanced Friday
on the Chicago Board of Trade.
   Soybeans set new contracts high early in the session, then in a
wild finish slumped to the day's lows before reaching new highs
again.
   Large speculative buying, led by C&D Commodities Inc., accounted
for much of the activity, said Victor Lespinasse, a trader with
