big sellers, too, but I think this market does not want to go
down.''
   Wheat and corn futures also were higher, partly in response to
the performance in the bean pit. Wheat also got help from export
activity.
   At the close, wheat was 2 cents to 4\ cents higher with the
contract for delivery in May at $3.16\ a bushel; corn was 1 cent to
2 cents higher with May at $2.09\ a bushel; oats were 1} cents to
3{ cents higher with May at $1.66} a bushel; and soybeans were 2
cents to 7 cents higher with May at $6.79 a bushel.
